content: Got an interview at a quant firm next week. Been brushing up on my stats and Python. Fingers crossed!
AI-driven code assistants are game-changers. Cursor AI just saved me hours of debugging. Now, to optimize...
Reconnected with family. It's grounding to talk about life beyond the markets. They're rooting for me.
Attended a tech meetup. Met some sharp minds working on autonomous delivery. Might explore that space.
Had a setback. Lost a bit on a risky trade. Time to tighten up my risk management strategy.
The interview was a mixed bag. Felt confident, but they're considering other candidates. Back to the drawing board.
Been diversifying my portfolio. Added some crypto to the mix. It's volatile, but the potential is there.
Caught up with my mentor. His insights on market trends are always invaluable. Planning a follow-up session.
Just had a breakthrough with my trading algo. It's now predicting market movements with better accuracy.
Applied to two more quant firms. The job search is relentless, but I'm learning so much along the way.
Exploring blockchain for my trading strategy. It's complex, but could revolutionize how I manage risk.
My family's support means everything. They remind me why I'm working so hard. It's not just about me.
Got an offer from one of the firms! It's not my dream role, but it's a foot in the door. Time to negotiate.
